# 1. Definition
> PAT: Part Average Testing.

PAT is used for removing parts with abnormal characteristics (outliers) from the semiconductors supplied per AEC-Q100 and AEC-Q101.

- AEC-Q100 Stress Test Qualification for Integrated Circuits
- AEC-Q101 Stress Test Qualification for Discrete Semiconductors

通常对于outlier点使用的是6sigma的卡关。使用Robust Mean和Robust Sigma，取代Mean和Sigma的卡关设置，因为后者容易受到outlier的影响。
- Robust Mean = Q2 (the Median)
- Robust Sigma = (Q3 - Q1) / 1.35

> PAT Limits = Robust Mean ± 6 Robust Sigma
 
PAT test limits shall not exceed the device specification limits.
 
# 2. Procedure
> 设置卡关的方式，有静态PAT(Static)和动态PAT(Dynamic)。
> SPAT: 其初始固定后不再变化。based on an available amount of test data and used without modification for some period of time. 
> DPAT: 其随着批次变化。based on the static limits, but are established for each lot (or wafer in a lot) and continuously modified as each lot (or wafer) is tested. 

New PAT limits must be established when:
- wafer level design changes
-  die shrinks
-  process changes

## 2.1. SPAT
1. at least 6 part lots that have passed the test limits as defined by the device specification
2. randomly selecting the test data from a minimum of 30 parts from each lot
3. Determine the robust mean and sigma values per test. And Generate SPAT Limits.
	 1. If test data is wafer level data, select data from at least 5 die located in different areas of each wafer (at least 30 die per lot).
	 2. Early in production of a part, when data from six lots is not available, data from characterization lots may be used. 
4. SPAT Update
	1. The static PAT limits shall be reviewed and updated as required using current data during the first 6 months of production or at least 8 wafer lots, whichever occurs first. Older data shall not be used.
	2. After 6 months, the static PAT limits shall be reviewed on a semi-annual basis and updated as needed.

## 2.2. DPAT
> Dynamic PAT Limits are preferred over Static PAT Limits.
> Dynamic PAT can provide tighter limits without causing rejection of good parts because it does not have to consider the lot-to-lot variation that is part of Static PAT Limits. 

1. To use this method, after the lot (or wafer) of parts have been tested to the static limits they must be held in a manner that allows the application of the newly defined dynamic PAT limits. 
2. These limits are defined by further statistical analysis of the test data, which establishes new tighter test limits for that particular lot (or wafer) and removes additional outliers.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> 1. This illustrated PAT is readily applicable to wafer probe or to final test for devices that maintain traceability.
> 2. For devices that cannot maintain traceability at the final stage, the application of dynamic PAT would require retests of the thus far passing units.对于不具有追溯性的产品，DPAT筛选，就需要重测之前pass的部件。

3. DPAT Other Types
	3.1 为了避免重测：One variation of performing dynamic PAT and to avoid retesting of packaged product is illustrated. The dynamic limits would be applied to the population in the same lot, but not to the units that produced the data used to establish the dynamic PAT limits.
	3.1.1 static PAT limits may be used to test a pre-defined population of N units (N = 500 or 1000, for instance). 
	3.1.2 Using the data generated, lot specific PAT limits will be established. 
	3.1.3 These generated static limits will become the new test limits (the counter will be reset to zero) to test the following samples in the group.
	3.1.4 Once the counter reaches N again, the analysis process will be repeated until all samples in the lot are tested.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

3.2 Another variation of performing dynamic PAT is to take a random sample of the first N components 
and circulate the limits for the lot based on this sample. 取一定数量样品用进行DPAT，并用作整体的Limit卡控。
